# LLM Implementation Agent — P12: Extension Runtime Host + Design System

**Version:** 2.5.0  
**Last Updated:** 2026-05-17  
**Purpose:** Extension runtime host (sandbox executor, permission model, agent injection, skill runner) and dashboard design system cleanup (design token unification, theme consistency, typography, mobile).

---

# Part 1 — Phase Plan

## 0. TL;DR / Compact Mental Model

**Phase:** `P12`  
**One-line goal:** Build a sandbox runtime host that can actually execute extensions and consolidate dashboard's scattered design tokens into a single source.  
**Why now:** P11 completed the UI shells. P12 puts a real engine behind those shells. Without extension runtime, P11.D/E workspaces are dead code. Without design system cleanup, every new dashboard component will compound token duplication.  
**Blast radius:** `packages/coding-agent/src/extensions/`, `packages/web-server/src/extensions-routes.ts`, `packages/web-server/src/skills-routes.ts`, `packages/web-ui/dashboard/src/` (60+ component, 35+ hook).  
**Rollback path:** Extension runtime can be disabled via `extensionRuntime.enabled: false` flag. Design system changes are purely Tailwind class swaps, CSS variables fallback preserved. Each workspace commits independently.  
**Scale mode:** `experimental_6`  
**Safe parallelism target:** 3  
**Done when:** Extension manifest is parsed and runs in sandbox, gets injected into the agent as a tool, skill runner executes steps. Dashboard 60+ components use a single `design-tokens.ts` source, no theme conflicts, 10px table issue resolved.

